n to the central themes in Hartmann's thought. There has been a recent renaissance of interest in his "new ontology"both as systematic theory and in philosophical anthropology. This text serves as an ideal introduction to Hartmann and as a supplement in courses on metaphysics, anthropology, and 20th century philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 4a20th century. 4aAnthropologie. 4aKategorienlehre. 4aNeo-Kantianism. 4aNeukantianismus. 4aOntologie. 4aOntology. 4aPhilosophie, 20. Jahrhundert. 4aanthropology. 4acategories of being. 4aphilosophy. 70(DE-601)1060853440(DE-588)4075660-9aOntologie2gnd 70(DE-601)1062002320(DE-588)4045798-9aPhilosophische Anthropologie2gnd 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh1 aHartung, Gerald, eeditor.1 aWunsch, Matthias, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103724650 cprintz978311029119340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110291209423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110291209.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DPHb2014  aZDB-23-GPHc2000d2014